{"ts":"2026-04-27T20:10:34.789Z","author":"codex-agent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/comments/1","value":{"created_at":"2026-04-27T20:10:34.789Z","author":"codex-agent","text":"Execution scope 2026-04-27 (mixed-wave): implement first-class normalize command in two slices. Slice A (dry-run): detect low-signal metadata/closure-like drift patterns and emit deterministic mutation previews sorted by item id/field, reusing governance policy primitives from validate and update-many planning semantics. Slice B (apply): execute approved normalization updates via safe mutation flow with explicit apply flag, preserving ownership semantics/history writes and avoiding non-deterministic side effects. Acceptance mapping: (1) scan/report = normalized findings + per-item planned field changes and summary counts; (2) deterministic preview = stable dry-run output contract suitable for agent automation (--json); (3) apply mode = history-backed updates through existing PM mutation pathways with clear result reporting and warnings."}},{"op":"replace","path":"/front_matter/updated_at","value":"2026-04-27T20:10:34.789Z"}],"before_hash":"b2f6be69e6054d0fe9b9d960f58a5a57983270962315d751d2f1db921f154d39","after_hash":"10d0b225e44bdf19b744d358643d25dccfaa25bd7245cddc48d6d71f245a613c"}
